consensus text: Oh could our spirits winged with flame
For sake their earth born chilly frame
And Yet [deletion][unclear]carry all[/unclear][/deletion] [insertion]preserve[/insertion] the thoughts that move
The ardent wish the strong desire
That burns for ever to aspire
Ah then how blissful would it be
To traverse nature's realm with thee
the earth, in ocean & [insertion]given[/insertion] in heaven,
To trace the laws, of power
